<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-01T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2746: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-01T20:00:00-05:00">December 1, 1933—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>130. Under headlines “Complete Liberation of the Country” <hi rend="italic">Haiti-Journal</hi> tonight publishes all documents
                            mentioned my telegram[s] 128 and 129.</p>
                        <p>I would appreciate information actual situation earliest possible
                            moment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>